  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg4154">msg4154 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: brittag</th>
   <th>Date: 2014-03-04.20:49:46</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Thanks for looking into this, hermitnoon!

It looks like this part of the CSS is controlled by the site-wide stylesheets instead of the blog-
specific stylesheets. See here: <a href="http://openhatch.org/static/less/base/base.less">http://openhatch.org/static/less/base/base.less</a> - h3 { margin-
bottom: 0px; text-align: left; clear: left; font-weight: normal; font-size: 1.1em; color: @default-
text-color; letter-spacing: 0; margin: 0; }

I figured this out because when I clicked "inspect element" in Chrome to look at this h3, the source 
of the styling appeared to be the page itself instead of an external CSS file - and I remembered that 
OpenHatch uses "less" - so some external CSS files get loaded into the page with JavaScript. So I 
looked at the "less" files at the top of the page HTML and found the one that had the right h3 
styling.

I don't know if simply changing that h3 styling will cause problems elsewhere on the OpenHatch site 
though - that sounds like something to investigate. :)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
